tweet: @MaunakeaVIS staff with a blooming 'ahinahina or silversword last summer.  #FunFactFriday, the silvery color comes from tiny hairs  on the leaves that reflect sunlight, essential protection on Maunakea to keep the plants from losing too much water.   #MaunakeaSilversword  https://t.co/dPMtLl3joh
